parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Sinking or Spongy Brake Pedal
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A brake pedal that sinks or feels spongy can lead to delayed or incomplete braking, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes below the accelerator pedal when applied
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle takes longer than usual to stop
the brakes make a hissing or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rusted brake lines can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to brake failure and increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks
rust or corrosion on brake lines
spongy or soft brake pedal
difficulty stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can increase the risk of injuries and fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
warning lights or messages on the dashboard indicating airbag system malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive vibration from the rear drive shaft can cause loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine knock or noise can indicate engine damage, potentially leading to engine failure and stranding.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tailgate support cable can cause the tailgate to fall unexpectedly, potentially causing injury or damage to the vehicle or surrounding objects.
